2. Upstream provenance
----------------------

The initial Chimera++ work was based on upstream release v1.2.34
(commit c1360294) and subsequent upstream commit a0506ae. At the time this
baseline was received, the upstream Cargo metadata declared MIT, while the
repository snapshot did not contain a root LICENSE or NOTICE file.

Upstream commit 7f72aec later added the GNU Affero General Public License
v3.0 and declared subsequent CodexPlusPlus versions AGPL-3.0-only. Its
upstream release notes state that versions previously received under another
license are not retroactively affected. Chimera++ adopts AGPL-3.0-only for
the modified distribution and for compatibility with future formal upstream
Release synchronization.

